We are on the hunt for our next cohort of graduates who will shape the future
of the energy industry. It is an exciting time to join our industry and
Stanwell’s Graduate Program offers the opportunity for growth and development
under the guidance of industry experts.

** About the position **

This is your opportunity to interact with people at all levels of our business
to help drive Energy Market’s strategy through fundamental market and data
analysis, continuous improvement initiatives and regular communication across
teams within the Energy Trading division.

  * Rotating across our Energy Market teams to broaden your exposure to the division 
  * Continually analyse energy markets and generate ideas 
  * Analyse data to improve our current strategies 
  * Prepare presentations of analysis of market 
  * Reporting on outcomes: Produce useful adhoc reports on historical outcomes and market events. 
  * Use market data to drive critical insights that feed into our strategies 
  * Building internal and external relationships to create influence, to achieve the Energy Markets strategic objectives. 

Please note this is a permanent position, complimented by a 3 year graduate
development program.

** What is in it for you? **

  * Be rewarded with a base salary of $109,382 in your first year, supplemented by a generous incentive scheme. 
  * Have access to professional memberships as well as an online learning management system to continually support your development. 
  * Take advantage of our discounted gym memberships and health insurance, voluntary health check reimbursements and various other exciting health and wellbeing initiatives. 
  * Be supported throughout your program by our mentors, subject matter experts and Graduate Program Coordinator. 

** Is this position for you? **

To make a meaningful contribution to our team, you will need:

  * A degree in a science or commercial related discipline. You must have graduated from this degree within the last two years. 
  * Strong quantitative background, to continually analyse the portfolio and market conditions 
  * Highly developed communication skills, with the ability to communicate at a variety of levels, internal and external to the organisation 
  * To Work under broad direction, independently or as part of a team, on activities that may be self-initiated while meeting milestones and timelines. 
  * A passion for learning with a positive attitude and ability to take initiative to achieve outcomes. 

** About Stanwell **

Stanwell provides the spark for a bright future, and that future starts now.
With our corporate office in Brisbane’s CBD and sites in the South Burnett and
Rockhampton regions, we are a supplier of energy solutions to Queensland, the
National Electricity Market, and large energy users throughout Australia. With
more than 3,000 MW of renewable generation projects and firming capacity under
development, we have an extensive renewable energy pipeline, with a goal of 9
to 10 GW of renewable energy and between 3 and 3.5 GW of energy storage in
place by 2035.

We care. We adapt. We deliver. These values are the driving force behind
everything we do. And as we grow and deliver that pipeline of projects in the
coming years, we will continue to serve our communities and deliver the power
that Queensland needs.

